author: Burkhart von Klitzing

text: One of many games I discover through their composers. As a fan of Hulsbeck (Turrican), it's quickly easy to hear that he's the one behind this soundtrack with his hard synths and drums. It seems like this is also a good shoot 'em up, though I've never played any Amiga games. The console certainly had some punch sound wise and provided us with top tier music.
